ks.\nActually, let me first check if there's a more efficient way. Maybe I can click on multiple green blocks at once, or maybe there's a pattern.\nLooking at the green block positions:\n- Row 7-11: 2 blocks at cols 19-23, 25-29 (cols 13-17 was just converted)\n- Row 13-17: 3 blocks at cols 13-17, 19-23, 25-29\n- Row 19-23: 2 blocks at cols 19-23, 25-29\n- Row 31-35: 4 blocks at cols 31-35, 37-41, 43-47, 49-53\nTotal: 2 + 3 + 2 + 4 = 11 green blocks\nLet me click on all 11 remaining green blocks in one batch.", "kind": "reasoning", "inContext": false}, {"label": "TOOL CALL: python", "content": "<tool_call>\n<function=python>\n<parameter=code>\n# Click on all remaining green blocks\n# Get current green block positions\nseg = current_frame.segmentation\nnodes = seg['nodes']\ngreen = [n for n in nodes if n['color'] == 'N']\n\nclicks = []\nfor n in green:\n    b = n['boundary']\n    min_r = min(p[0] for p in b)\n    max_r = max(p[0] for p in b)\n    min_c = min(p[1] for p in b)\n    max_c = max(p[1] for p in b)\n    center_r = (min_r + max_r) // 2\n    center_c = (min_c + max_c) // 2\n    clicks.append({'action': 'MOUSE', 'row': center_r, 'col': center_c})\n\nprint(f\"Clicking {len(clicks)} green blocks\")\naction(clicks)\n</parameter>\n</function>\n</tool_call>", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "TOOL RESULT: python", "content": "Clicking 11 green blocks", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}], "hasExactModelContext": false, "requestIndexWithinTurn": null, "messageCount": 0}, "context": {"sections": [{"label": "USER PROMPT", "content": "The code executed 1 action in the previous sequence.\nExecuted actions: MOUSE(row=9, col=15).\nYou are still on the same level.\nCurrent state: step 42, level 1.\nValid actions right now: LEFT, RIGHT, MOUSE, ACTION7.\nOnly tool: `python`. It receives `current_frame`, `previous_frame`, `history`, `transitions`, `last_transition`, `valid_actions`, `last_action_result`, and `action(actions)`. It also provides `last_animation` (p